{"id":181,"date":"2015-06-19T10:16:11","date_gmt":"2015-06-19T04:46:11","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/ewokesoft.com\/blog\/?p=132"},"modified":"2015-06-19T10:16:11","modified_gmt":"2015-06-19T04:46:11","slug":"magento-sort-latest-product-by-created-date-and-new-from-date","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ewokesoft.com\/magento-sort-latest-product-by-created-date-and-new-from-date\/","title":{"rendered":"Magento: Sort latest product by created date and new from date"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Here is a quick tip to sort\/order latest product by both created date and new from date.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Created At date<\/strong> is automatically added when you add a new product. However, you have to set <strong>New from Date<\/strong> manually while adding or editing product.<\/p>\n<p>You may have product with same <strong>new from date<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>And, then you need <strong>created at<\/strong> date to sort the latest product.<\/p>\n<p>Here is the code to sort\/order product by both created date and new from date:<\/p>\n<pre>$todayDate = Mage::app()-&gt;getLocale()-&gt;date()-&gt;toString(Varien_Date::DATETIME_INTERNAL_FORMAT);\n$collection = Mage::getModel('catalog\/product')\n -&gt;getCollection()\n -&gt;addAttributeToFilter('news_from_date', array('date' =&gt; true, 'to' =&gt; $todayDate))\n -&gt;addAttributeToFilter('news_to_date', array('or'=&gt; array(\n 0 =&gt; array('date' =&gt; true, 'from' =&gt; $todayDate),\n 1 =&gt; array('is' =&gt; new Zend_Db_Expr('null')))\n ), 'left')\n -&gt;addAttributeToSort('news_from_date', 'desc')\n -&gt;addAttributeToSort('created_at', 'desc');<\/pre>\n<p>Hope this code will help you. Thanks.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Here is a quick tip to sort\/order latest product by both created date and new from date. Created At date is automatically added when you add a new product. However, you have to set New from Date manually while adding or editing product. You may have product with 